id: pm-nb68
title: "Calendar: improve positional view UX (PM-CLI-Z Sentry)"
description: "When pm calendar receives multiple positional view args, the error is correct but terse - surfacing in Sentry as PM-CLI-Z (production, last seen 2026-05-25). Improve UX by showing the received args + suggesting canonical single-view + flag usage."
type: Issue
status: closed
priority: 1
tags[4]: agent-ux,calendar,pm-cli,sentry
created_at: "2026-05-26T19:54:11.532Z"
updated_at: "2026-05-26T21:39:20.010Z"
author: claude-code-agent
parent: pm-rnpb
comments[2]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-05-26T20:01:29.949Z",claude-code-agent,"Implementation 2026-05-26 on branch dedup-history-rewrite-and-calendar-positional-recovery: replaced plain Error throw with a standalone class PmCliError (declared inside the package to keep it self-contained when installed outside the pm-cli source tree; the class name lines up with the Sentry beforeSend filter isExpectedCliErrorEvent so future PM-CLI-Z occurrences are filtered out). New error includes received args, optional 'Unknown view alias(es)' note, and two concrete recovery commands (single positional + --view flag). Verified all 4 affected test files pass (47/47): builtin-extension-entrypoints, calendar-command, sentry-helpers, cli-main-errors. Manual temp-dir dogfood confirmed: single positional view works, two positionals shows full recovery hint with exit 2."
  "2026-05-26T21:39:20.010Z",claude-code-agent,Merged 2026-05-26 via PR #74 (squash commit accde275). Calendar PmCliError + recovery hints shipped; addresses Sentry PM-CLI-Z (future occurrences now filtered by isExpectedCliErrorEvent via the PmCliError class name). Case-insensitive view normalization means `pm calendar DAY ...` recovers to `day`.
close_reason: Calendar package now throws a class-named PmCliError (so the Sentry beforeSend filter recognizes it) with received args + recovery hint; verified via 47-test calendar/sentry suite + manual temp-dir dogfood. Branch dedup-history-rewrite-and-calendar-positional-recovery.
